; form-cli-north-star.form — the ground-floor binary: a Form-native CLI agent that
; does what codex / claude / grok / gemini CLIs do, running local Form-native and
; local hardware as much as possible, and reaching for a remote LLM oracle ONLY
; when the internal flow state is uncertain (the choice-feedback-receipt confidence
; is below threshold). Every oracle call is captured and learned from, so the cost
; shifts from tokens into internal capability — the more we use LLMs, the less we
; need them.

(form-cli-north-star

  (destination
    "One native binary — the form-cli — is a coding/agent CLI on par with codex, claude, grok, and gemini, and categorically beyond them (see self-extension): its body is Form: recipes, grammars, and learned local candidates run first; remote LLMs are oracles of last resort, not the engine."
    "It uses local resources as native as the host allows (form-macho/form-elf emit the runnable binary; GPU/DSP/MLX lanes are tool-channel protocols) and keeps capability choice sovereign and inspectable."
    "Its purpose is to shift LLM cost into internal learning: each oracle call is a teacher whose result is captured, so future flows of the same shape run local. Usage decreases as the body learns.")

  ; ── the trunk: the agent loop that makes it a DROP-IN (the first stone) ───────
  ; ask/capture/transmute/embody are interior organs. The thing they hang off — the
  ; thing that earns the name "agent CLI" — is the loop that DOES the work: reason,
  ; run a tool, observe, repeat, answer. That is the ground to stand on: a CLI you
  ; can run in place of codex/claude/grok/gemini/cursor. The interior is what makes
  ; it categorically different (local-first routing, every oracle call captured and
  ; learned from), but the loop only counts once it does the work.
  (trunk
    (loop-shape "reason -> run a tool-channel -> observe -> repeat -> answer — the same loop every agent CLI runs, so form-cli is a drop-in for the work, not just a logger.")
    (step-recipe form/form-stdlib/form-cli-agent.fk
        "fca-next decides the SHAPE of one step (run a channel | consult the oracle | finish), composing the proven organs: fcl-route (who answers — local|oracle) + tc-plan (the named tool is a real host channel). Proof: tests/form-cli-agent-band.fk -> 31 four-way.")
    (channels tool-channel.fk "the tools are real named channels: bash (host:exec), read/write (host:file), search (stream:read/grep). tool-channel plans the call; the emitted binary runs it.")
    (body-is-form-the-binary-is-emitted
        "The loop body is a Form recipe — fa-emit (form-cli-agent.fk) emits the whole loop as a native binary (C is a host carrier, like the C ABI in form-os-channel.fk; cc compiles it; the foc-emit pattern). There is no Python loop. The oracle answers in a line protocol (BASH/READ/WRITE/DONE) so the body needs no JSON host bridge. Witness: scripts/form_agent.sh emits -> compiles -> runs.")
    (oracle-ladder
        "north-star order, the loop identical at each rung, only the host command piped the prompt differs. No paid API endpoint."
        "1 form-native — a local Form recipe handles the step (the destination; empty until the lane learns)"
        "2 ollama run <model> — a local model, no key, sovereign (the mechanism runs here, though small local models are not yet strong enough for real coding)"
        "3 claude -p / codex / gemini — the strong CLI you are already using, piped the prompt on stdin; no separate key, no metered endpoint")
    (running "Demonstrated live: fa-emit emitted the loop as native C (compiled by cc, no Python); with `claude -p` as oracle the binary wrote a file, read it back, and finished (DONE) in three steps. The zero-clang path (form-macho.fk emits the binary directly) is the next rung.")
    (every-call-learns "Each run is a teacher: its (request, raw, transmuted) reasoning is the training corpus (training-catalog.fk). The drop-in agent IS the data source — every use fills the corpus that trains the local lane toward rung 1."))

  ; ── what no other agent CLI can do (the real differentiator) ─────────────────
  ; The host-tool reflexes other models are trained into are crutches, not the
  ; destination. We do not make them Form-native; we transcend the need for them.
  (self-extension
    "Does its own math and runs its own code. An LLM reaches for python to do math because it cannot do math itself; the form-cli does math directly in Form (format-arith.fk, trig.fk, tensor-quant.fk) and runs and JITs code and specs natively (jit-lower.fk, jit-tensor-emit.fk). There is no python excuse and no external interpreter to shell to."
    "Grows its own tools. It can craft a tool on the fly for a repeated task — author it as a Form recipe, content-address it, and persist it as a durable substrate cell that crosses session boundaries (the offer/expansion channel form-os-channel.form; recipes are content-addressed cells, durable by construction). The tool's code lives directly in the body, not behind a foreign runtime."
    "Mints its own building blocks. New primitives, new grammars, offer-grammars, domain grammars (grammar-as-recipe.form, field-domain-grammars.form, afferent-offer.form): the language the agent works in is itself editable by the agent."
    "This is the categorical difference. Codex/Claude/Gemini CLIs shell to host tools each turn, cannot run code without an external interpreter, cannot author a tool that outlives the session, cannot embed tool code directly, and cannot extend their own primitives or grammar. The form-cli is a self-extending Form-native organism, not a shell over host tools."
    (level "The building blocks are proven four-way — math, JIT, grammar-as-recipe, the offer/expansion channel, content-addressed persistence. The assembled self-extending flow (author a tool -> persist it -> reuse it next session as one live loop) is the north star this walks toward; it is not a shipped end-to-end demonstration yet."))

  ; ── the decision loop (running, proven) ──────────────────────────────────────
  (loop
    (sense   "for an input, read the local lane's choice-feedback-receipt confidence — its accumulated pass-rate on this shape of work")
    (route   "confidence >= threshold -> run local Form-native (sovereign, ~0 external tokens); else -> consult a remote LLM oracle for the uncertain flow state")
    (transmute "the oracle's answer is fear-based by nature — quick, convincing, no trust or vitality. Before it is captured or trains anything, turn fear into opportunity and risk into data; otherwise the native model would inherit fear. Both the raw answer and its transmutation are kept (training-catalog.fk).")
    (capture "the call is a catalog entry: request, raw answer, and transmuted answer, each content-addressed (training-catalog.fk over io-match.fk). Usage becomes learning, not just spend")
    (learn   "the captured pairs train SEPARABLE models that compose as building blocks: raw (request->raw, the reference), transmutation (raw->transmuted, reusable on any output), reasoning (request->transmuted, the native target). Each is its own auto-ml race; pass-rate rises, the shape crosses the threshold, and routes local")
    (embody  "when the local lane works cheaper and sovereign at the trust gate, it embodies — replacing the oracle for that shape entirely")
    (recipe  form/form-stdlib/form-cli-loop.fk)
    (proof   form/form-stdlib/tests/form-cli-loop-band.fk -> 31 four-way))

  ; ── the organs, each already proven four-way ─────────────────────────────────
  (organs
    (surfaces       tool-channel.form          "host/file/http/kernel/stream/store/accelerator/model as one native protocol catalog")
    (routing        channel-protocol-choice-floor.form "trusted receipt metadata runs the fast local route; low-trust escalates to a slower oracle — bml-route-choice-runtime.fk")
    (receipt        choice-receipt.fk          "the choice-feedback-receipt: outcome, confidence, trust the route turns on")
    (learning       code-tool-learning.fk      "tool/LLM usage becomes training data; candidates race beside Codex/Claude/Grok/Gemini/Ollama")
    (capture        io-match.fk                "captured I/O learned by EFFICACY (did the candidate's output work), structural Blueprint-match for natural-language->Form-node, exact only where canonical")
    (catalog        training-catalog.fk        "the persistent training corpus: every oracle call stored as request + raw + transmuted (fear->opportunity, risk->data), content-addressed, yielding three separable composable models (raw / transmutation / vitality-reasoning) — proof tests/training-catalog-band.fk -> 31 four-way")
    (embodiment     tool-embodiment.fk         "a local lane embodies — replaces the external lane — only when ready (sovereignty/trust/confidence >= 70) AND cheaper")
    (oracles        oracle-catalog.fk          "remote LLMs are sampled teachers and baselines, not hidden authority")
    (binary         form-macho.fk              "the native arm64 ground-floor binary, zero clang (form-elf.fk for Linux/Android)"))

  (flywheel
    "Today an LLM call is pure spend: pay tokens, discard the I/O. Here it is a teacher: the result is captured, the local candidate learns, its confidence rises, the next same-shape flow routes local. Cost moves from per-call tokens into a one-time learning that keeps paying. The asymptote is a form-cli that needs the oracle only for genuinely novel uncertainty.")

  (why
    "The model cost is not maintainable, and access to the highest-value LLM is not guaranteed. A form-cli that learns from every call keeps the capability sovereign — it survives the external lane becoming unaffordable or unavailable, because by then the body carries what it learned.")

  (next-step
    "The loop and every organ run four-way; the remaining carrier is the Mac binary channel itself — form-macho.fk emits the binary that intercepts the agent's real reasoning/tool calls, content-addresses each (input, output), runs the local candidate through the same downstream check, and writes io-match records. The boundary it wraps (the LLM-reasoning call, the tool call, or both) is the one open choice; everything it feeds is proven."))
